The paper deals with the construction of secure substitution boxes (S-boxes) for use in elliptic curve cryptography (ECC), which is a topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method involves the use of Mordell elliptic curves (MECs) over finite fields, which is a topic in algebraic geometry and number theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper presents computational results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method, which is a topic in statistical computing and data analysis (cs.SD) and machine learning (cs.LG).
